PN,43702
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F437A1777299067
OL,3,CStalking: Investigating a crime that
OL,4,Cleaves victims living in constant fear
OL,6,FYou see, stalking happens even while
OL,7,Fthe perpetrator sleeps. Victims find
OL,8,Fthemselves in a state of hyper-
OL,9,Fvigilance and alertness; yet still,
OL,10,Faccording to charities, up to 100
OL,11,Finstances take place before the victim
OL,12,Fwill reach out to police.
OL,14,FI wanted to help us all understand -
OL,15,Fbeyond our preconceptions -what
OL,16,Fstalking is, to explain the frequent
OL,17,Freluctance of victims to call it out,
OL,18,Fand to find out what's being done to
OL,19,Ftackle it.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/7
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
