OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,438,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43707
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F437A1777299067
OL,3,CStalking: Investigating a crime that
OL,4,Cleaves victims living in constant fear
OL,6,FExperts now say it's time for still
OL,7,Fgreater progress. They say we must
OL,8,Fsimplify the law, train police so that
OL,9,Fvictims will be treated the same no
OL,10,Fmatter where they live, and raise
OL,11,Fpublic awareness so that stalking is
OL,12,Funiversally understood.
OL,14,FAs someone told me - stalking is not
OL,15,Fjust a crime, it's a warning sign.
OL,17,FWhat should you do if you think you're
OL,18,Fbeing stalked?
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G7/7
